Irrespective of the aforementioned cases, there will be relative errors, more or less. The main reasons for these cases can be expatiated as follows:


For simplifying the analysis, the parameter D is omitted in the calculations above;

The high order items for θ and the deformation in the axial direction of every leaf are still deleted;

Assumed trigonometric functions for small angle rotation are used;

The decomposed axial load p on every leaf is treated as zero.
